Colombia Stocks: Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana, Nutresa

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-06-13T21:41:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/colombia-stocks-grupo-de-inversiones-suramericana-nutresa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 1.1 percent, the most in a month, to
14,248.27, while the Colcap Index declined 1.2 percent to 1,730.  Grupo Nutresa SA (NUTRESA CB),  Colombia ’s biggest food
producer, fell 1 percent to 22,760 pesos, extending its losing
streak to three days. The company on June 10 began selling 25
million shares for 20,900 pesos each, 16 percent less than the
June 8 closing price.  Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana (GRUPOSUR CB), the parent
company of Colombia’s largest bank, fell 7.2 percent, the most
since October 2008, to 38,920 pesos. The company said June 10
after the market closed that its board will seek to convert some
existing ordinary shares into stock with preferential dividend
payments.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
